parameters.name: domainIdentifier
parameters.description: The identifier of the Amazon DataZone domain.

nested_items.name: items
nested_items.description: The results of the ListEnvironmentProfiles action.

nested_items.name: awsAccountId
nested_items.description: The identifier of an Amazon Web Services account in which an environment profile exists.

nested_items.name: awsAccountRegion
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services Region in which an environment profile exists.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The timestamp of when an environment profile was created.

nested_items.name: createdBy
nested_items.description: The Amazon DataZone user who created the environment profile.

nested_items.name: description
nested_items.description: The description of the environment profile.

nested_items.name: domainId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the Amazon DataZone domain in which the environment profile exists.

nested_items.name: environmentBlueprintId
nested_items.description: The identifier of a blueprint with which an environment profile is created.

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: The identifier of the environment profile.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the environment profile.

nested_items.name: projectId
nested_items.description: The identifier of a project in which an environment profile exists.

nested_items.name: updatedAt
nested_items.description: The timestamp of when the environment profile was updated.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: When the number of environment profiles is greater than the default value for the MaxResults parameter, or if you explicitly specify a value for MaxResults that is less than the number of environment profiles, the response includes a pagination token named NextToken. You can specify this NextToken value in a subsequent call to ListEnvironmentProfiles to list the next set of environment profiles.
